<section id="help" class="card">
<h2>How you can help owls</h2>
<ul>
<li>Protect and restore native habitat — preserve old trees and hedgerows used for nesting.</li>
<li>Install owl boxes where appropriate — they provide safe nesting sites in areas lacking cavities.</li>
<li>Reduce rodenticide use — poisons move up the food chain and harm owls.</li>
<li>Drive carefully at dusk and dawn — many collisions happen near roads where prey is abundant.</li>
<li>Support local conservation groups — donations, volunteering, and reporting injured birds help directly.</li>
</ul>
</section>


<section class="card">
<h2>Fun facts</h2>
<div class="grid-3">
<div class="feature"><h3>Owls swallow prey whole</h3><p class="tag">Regurgitated pellets help scientists study diets without harming animals.</p></div>
<div class="feature"><h3>They are not always nocturnal</h3><p class="tag">Some species, like burrowing owls and snowy owls, are active during the day.</p></div>
<div class="feature"><h3>Some owls migrate</h3><p class="tag">Movement depends on food availability and species — not all are migratory.</p></div>
</div>
</section>


